<P><H1 align=center>DC270 - ADD/EDIT BANK/BUILDING SOCIETY DETAILS</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red>Areas shown in red text are mandatory 
and must be completed to proceed.</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Building society name: </H3>The directory search button 
will take you to a screen that allows you to search for the name of the company 
you want to input. Input the name of the company and click on directory search. 
Select the correct address from the list shown and click on ‘select’, this will 
transfer the details already held to the details screen. If the company name is 
not on the Directory search, you will need to type it in the field manually.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Branch name: </H3>If the company name is in the 
directory, the branch name will be automatically populated. The Bank wizard 
button will validate the sort code and account number, to ensure they have the 
correct number of digits for that Bank/Building society.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is in the directory: </H3>Click ‘No’ if the company is 
not in the search directory.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Account salary paid into:</H3>Does the applicant have 
his salary paid into the account detailed.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Sort code, account number and account name: </H3>All 
details should be provided by the applicant and are mandatory fields.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Time at bank/building society: </H3>Complete with the 
period of time the applicant held the account in question.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Repayment account: </H3>Click if this is the account 
that mortgage payments will be made from.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Proposed method of repayment: </H3>This will only be 
active of the Repayment account question has been ticked ‘Yes’. Select the 
method of repayment from the drop down list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>DD reference: </H3>Input the name or number that will 
be used as a reference for collection of payments.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Proposed repayment date: </H3>The date that payments 
will be made by whatever method was selected.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Address: </H3>If the company is found in the directory 
search, the address fields of the branch will be automatically populated. If 
not, input the post code and click on the P.A.F search button. Select the 
address required and click on <STRONG>Select</STRONG>, this will populate the 
address in the relevant address fields. Click on the <STRONG>Clear 
</STRONG>        
            
              
             
       button to delete all address fields.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Contact details: </H3>Input all details known, once 
completed you can add the address and contact details to the directory by 
clicking on the <STRONG>Add </STRONG>     
             
    to directory button.
<P></P>
<P>Click <STRONG>OK </STRONG>  when all details completed.</P>
